Subject: Disable (not just demote) the physical primary during EVDI streaming

Patch 0002 made the EVDI virtual display kscreen's priority-1 output, and
demoted the prior physical primary (e.g. DP-3) to priority 2. That was
enough to route new windows to the EVDI display IF kwin's per-output-combo
state in ~/.config/kwinoutputconfig.json agreed.

But ~/.config/kwinoutputconfig.json holds saved setups keyed by the set of
connected outputs. When EVDI hotplugs, kwin first applies whichever saved
setup matches the new combo — which on this user's box was a stale
dual-GPU-era entry that re-promoted DP-3 to primary. Our patch 0002 then
overwrites it, but Steam / game launchers had already cached "primary
output = DP-3" and continued spawning windows there. Invisible to the
Steam Deck stream.

Surgically removing the stale setup helps, but it's not durable — kwin
saves new setups whenever the output topology changes, so a future stale
entry could resurrect the problem.

Belt + braces fix: DISABLE the physical primary during the stream entirely.
The desktop becomes "EVDI display only" for the duration of the session.
Steam, games, every window manager heuristic has no other surface to land
on. When the stream ends, on_evdi_removed re-enables AND re-promotes the
saved original primary back, restoring the user's normal desktop.

The disable + enable both go through a single kscreen-doctor invocation
(with `output.<x>.enable output.<x>.priority.1` chained) so the atomic
apply avoids any frame where the user has no primary at all.

Affects only Apollo streaming sessions (createVirtualDisplay -> remove).
Other workflows (gamescope, normal desktop usage) are untouched.

--- a/src/platform/linux/virtual_display.cpp
+++ b/src/platform/linux/virtual_display.cpp
@@ -466,9 +466,18 @@
                       << " (saved old primary: "
                       << (saved_primary.empty() ? "<none>" : saved_primary) << ")";
 
+      // Also DISABLE the physical primary during the stream. Without this,
+      // kwin remembers per-output-combo configs in ~/.config/kwinoutputconfig.json
+      // and may re-mark the physical monitor as primary at session start,
+      // before our priority-promote runs. Steam and game launchers then
+      // spawn windows on the physical display instead of the EVDI virtual
+      // one — invisible to the Steam Deck stream. Disabling the physical
+      // output entirely forces windows onto the EVDI display. The disable
+      // is reversed in on_evdi_removed() so the user's normal desktop
+      // returns when the stream ends.
       std::string cmd = "kscreen-doctor output." + new_name + ".enable output." + new_name + ".priority.1";
       if (!saved_primary.empty() && is_safe_name(saved_primary)) {
-        cmd += " output." + saved_primary + ".priority.2";
+        cmd += " output." + saved_primary + ".disable";
       }
       const int rc = run_status(cmd);
       if (rc != 0) {
@@ -483,9 +492,13 @@
       }
       if (evdi_active_count == 0 && !saved_primary.empty()) {
         if (is_safe_name(saved_primary)) {
-          const std::string cmd = "kscreen-doctor output." + saved_primary + ".priority.1";
+          // Re-enable AND promote the original primary back. Order matters
+          // here: kscreen-doctor applies the commands as one atomic update,
+          // so enable + priority.1 in the same call avoids a flicker where
+          // the user has no primary output for a brief moment.
+          const std::string cmd = "kscreen-doctor output." + saved_primary + ".enable output." + saved_primary + ".priority.1";
           run_status(cmd);
-          BOOST_LOG(info) << "[VDISPLAY] Restored kscreen primary to: " << saved_primary;
+          BOOST_LOG(info) << "[VDISPLAY] Restored kscreen primary to: " << saved_primary << " (re-enabled and promoted)";
         }
         saved_primary.clear();
       }
